race.description: Country Championships At Mtc Feb 28 Maiden Plate
race.comment: BELNERA (6) drifted back from a good draw last time then wound up strongly to score with a bit in hand over the 1400m here. Frater stays on and is well placed to make it two on the bounce. UNDERCUT (5) was a determined on pace maiden winner when resuming in December. Not as effective last time but looks ready for the rise to the mile. SABATINA (7) has been racing well and is poised to break through after six minor placings in a row. Goes well at this journey and has been in the placings at all four tries and shapes as a key runner. RIVERBEND UNICORN (2) proved too strong two runs ago but was less impressive last time out when fourth here. Boudvillain sticking is a good push, so willing to give another go.
